# Layer 5 - Session

## Overview

This task introduced the Session Layer, which is Layer 5 of the OSI Model. The Session Layer is responsible for establishing, maintaining, and terminating communication sessions between devices. It ensures that connections remain active while data is being exchanged and manages session recovery through checkpoints.

---

## Objectives

* Understand the purpose of the Session Layer.
* Learn how sessions are established between devices.
* Understand session management and maintenance.
* Learn the role of checkpoints in communication.
* Understand how sessions are terminated.

