## Key Findings / Notes

* The Session Layer is Layer 5 of the OSI Model.
* It establishes communication sessions between devices.
* Sessions remain active while connections are active.
* The Session Layer maintains and monitors active connections.
* It terminates sessions when connections are lost or inactive.
* Checkpoints help recover communication efficiently.
* Only missing data needs to be retransmitted after a checkpoint.
* Every session is unique and independent.

